Jordan May Get Increase in World Bank Loan, Jordan Times Reports

-- B y   M o h a m m a d   T a y s e e r
-- 
2011-08-18T07:33:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/jordan-may-get-increase-in-world-bank-loan-jordan-times-reports.html
The  World Bank  will decide next
month whether to give Jordan a $250 million loan to support the
countryâ€™s state budget,  the Jordan Times reported today , citing
Jafar Hassan, the minister of planning and international
cooperation.  The kingdom applied for a $150 million loan in 2010,
increasing the amount to $250 million later, the newspaper said.
The loan, with an interest rate of 1.25 percent and a maturity
period of more than 20 years, would be used to support the
budget and economic and social reforms, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
